The services in the Pontifical part of the Sacramentary have generally no rubrics or very short ones. They agree

Of the Masses contained in this part of the volume, I have found 250 in the Sacramentaries edited by Muratori, viz. . 234 in the Gregorian, 20 in the Gelasian, and 1 in the Leonine. Of, the remainder, 16 occur in the Sacramentary edited by Menard, and 6 in the Sacramentary of Alcuin as edited by Pamelius3 4 in other Sacramentaries in the same volume 3 4 are mixed, and 17 1 have as yet been unable to find in any early Collection.

Of the Masses in the Gregorian Sacramentary of Muratori, all but 19 are in Leofric. Of the other Offices in the MS„

some are wholly from the Gelasian, and one or two much nearer to the Leonine than to the Gelasian or Gregorian.
